1
00:00:00,734 --> 00:00:05,906
EAST JERUSALEM

2
00:00:09,015 --> 00:00:10,705
We're on the grounds of Al Aqsa.

3
00:00:10,789 --> 00:00:13,904
It's one of the holiest
places in the Islamic religion.

4
00:00:14,047 --> 00:00:18,550
And so, we've come here, today on
one of the holiest nights of Ramadan.

5
00:00:18,634 --> 00:00:20,189
The crowds are huge.

6
00:00:20,308 --> 00:00:22,102
So, if anything happens,

7
00:00:22,186 --> 00:00:25,014
it could potentially be very
dangerous to the people that are here.

8
00:00:26,130 --> 00:00:28,842
It's night-time prayers
for Palestinian Muslims.

9
00:00:28,992 --> 00:00:32,203
And this year, Israeli forces
showed up unannounced.

10
00:00:33,174 --> 00:00:38,149
If we pray until dawn,
we will be obeying God's command.

11
00:00:43,471 --> 00:00:46,288
So, you can see that there's
Israeli police actually inside,

12
00:00:46,312 --> 00:00:47,332
in the grounds of Al Aqsa.

13
00:00:47,381 --> 00:00:49,082
That's what triggered the protests.

14
00:00:49,159 --> 00:00:50,967
And that's what triggered the anger today.

15
00:00:51,068 --> 00:00:52,598
If your only sacrifice for Al Aqsa

16
00:00:52,686 --> 00:00:55,136
is getting arrested or suffering,
that's worth it for defending it.

17
00:00:55,322 --> 00:00:58,735
Palestinians feel like they're
being pushed out of East Jerusalem,

18
00:00:58,859 --> 00:01:02,015
the city they see as the capital
of a future Palestinian state.

19
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:06,567
They say Israel is upping its efforts
to redraw the borders of the city.

20
00:01:06,934 --> 00:01:09,377
But Israel claims it belongs to them

21
00:01:09,503 --> 00:01:12,752
despite the United Nations
saying that it's an occupation,

22
00:01:12,908 --> 00:01:15,022
illegal under international law.

23
00:01:15,342 --> 00:01:19,112
The Israeli police have been arresting
loads of Palestinian children.

24
00:01:19,150 --> 00:01:21,055
The Palestinians are retaliating

25
00:01:21,215 --> 00:01:24,832
because so many young men
have been taken away by the police.

26
00:01:25,405 --> 00:01:27,316
Stop! Stop!

27
00:01:27,955 --> 00:01:29,724
Stop! Hold him!

28
00:01:29,808 --> 00:01:33,543
People just came here to worship,
and you're giving them shit!

29
00:01:33,633 --> 00:01:36,084
Fuck you all!
Do what you want.

30
00:01:36,168 --> 00:01:38,093
Come and arrest me!

31
00:01:38,184 --> 00:01:39,298
How old are you?

32
00:01:39,322 --> 00:01:40,699
How old are you?

33
00:01:40,754 --> 00:01:43,122
-15 years old.
-15 years old? Why are they taking you?

34
00:01:44,603 --> 00:01:48,927
God is great!

35
00:01:49,481 --> 00:01:51,210
Why do you think they took him?

36
00:01:51,545 --> 00:01:52,321
Why?

37
00:01:52,369 --> 00:01:53,662
They want to keep the young people away.

38
00:01:53,746 --> 00:01:55,947
They want to remove all
young people, one by one.

39
00:01:57,057 --> 00:01:58,518
As Ramadan continued,

40
00:01:58,685 --> 00:02:03,090
Palestinians in East Jerusalem faced
stun grenades, arrests, and water cannons,

41
00:02:03,464 --> 00:02:05,925
some of the worst violence seen in years.

42
00:02:06,817 --> 00:02:08,727
Go away! Go away!

43
00:02:10,531 --> 00:02:12,034
They sprayed us with water.

44
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:14,439
We were walking and not doing anything.

45
00:02:15,387 --> 00:02:17,597
They're dogs and animals.

46
00:02:19,098 --> 00:02:23,225
Come on, move. Don't scream.
Don't ever forget this.

47
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,344
Don't you ever forget what they did.

48
00:02:28,662 --> 00:02:32,007
East Jerusalem is important to
Jews, Muslims, and Christians.

49
00:02:32,221 --> 00:02:34,971
It's also the site of the
sacred Jewish Temple Mount.

50
00:02:35,133 --> 00:02:38,971
But most of the people who live in
this part of the city are Palestinians.

51
00:02:39,793 --> 00:02:41,363
That's been slowly changing

52
00:02:41,428 --> 00:02:44,508
since Israel captured the area in 1967

53
00:02:44,613 --> 00:02:46,643
and started moving in settlers.

54
00:02:47,518 --> 00:02:51,311
Jewish people now make up
around 40 percent of the population.

55
00:02:51,631 --> 00:02:53,241
And in 2018,

56
00:02:53,307 --> 00:02:55,609
Israel was emboldened by President Trump.

57
00:02:55,728 --> 00:02:59,555
He moved the US Embassy
into East Jerusalem from Tel Aviv.

58
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:01,949
It outraged Palestinians

59
00:03:02,029 --> 00:03:04,388
but was celebrated by right-wing Israelis.

60
00:03:04,455 --> 00:03:05,485
It is time…

61
00:03:05,953 --> 00:03:09,580
to officially recognize Jerusalem…

62
00:03:09,966 --> 00:03:12,610
as the capital of Israel.

63
00:03:13,028 --> 00:03:15,459
At the heart of the fight
over East Jerusalem

64
00:03:15,579 --> 00:03:17,705
is the neighborhood of Sheikh Jarrah,

65
00:03:17,789 --> 00:03:20,134
home mostly to Palestinian families,

66
00:03:20,218 --> 00:03:22,819
some who came here in 1956

67
00:03:22,936 --> 00:03:27,303
after being displaced by Israel when
the state was created eight years earlier.

68
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:30,450
Israel claims Jews
historically owned this land.

69
00:03:30,548 --> 00:03:34,102
Now, there's a lawsuit to forcibly
evict some Palestinian residents

70
00:03:34,127 --> 00:03:35,808
making its way through the courts.

71
00:03:36,029 --> 00:03:39,155
Even if you capture, kill,
and destroy our homes,

72
00:03:39,239 --> 00:03:42,608
you won't defeat our resolve!

73
00:03:43,211 --> 00:03:44,825
Protesters have been turning up

74
00:03:44,834 --> 00:03:47,157
since the issue reached
the Supreme Court this year.

75
00:03:47,568 --> 00:03:49,159
We will take our freedom!

76
00:03:49,475 --> 00:03:51,290
We will take our freedom!

77
00:03:52,086 --> 00:03:57,927
The Zionist organizations seized the
first house five months after the war.

78
00:03:58,005 --> 00:04:00,667
The first house they seized
back in November 1967

79
00:04:00,691 --> 00:04:02,455
belonged to the Shanti family.

80
00:04:02,816 --> 00:04:04,351
Muna Al Kurd and her relatives

81
00:04:04,376 --> 00:04:07,931
are one of 28 families fighting
in court to keep their homes.

82
00:04:08,349 --> 00:04:11,466
Believe me, no person from
the neighborhood will leave

83
00:04:11,550 --> 00:04:13,332
until they drag us out
at the last moment.

84
00:04:13,416 --> 00:04:16,410
We want to live! This is our house!
This is our land!

85
00:04:19,661 --> 00:04:23,364
Other Palestinians are already being
replaced by right-wing Israeli settlers.

86
00:04:23,448 --> 00:04:24,232
What's happening?

87
00:04:24,316 --> 00:04:25,661
Go away!

88
00:04:28,154 --> 00:04:29,367
Hey! Hey!

89
00:04:29,451 --> 00:04:30,669
Don't touch me.

90
00:04:32,410 --> 00:04:33,719
Don't touch me.

91
00:04:33,774 --> 00:04:35,142
We don't want any trouble.

92
00:04:38,037 --> 00:04:40,107
What happened exactly?

93
00:04:40,614 --> 00:04:43,717
Some young Palestinian boys and girls
were standing there,

94
00:04:44,037 --> 00:04:46,974
then that guy attacked them with a stick.
Look at it in his hand.

95
00:04:47,058 --> 00:04:48,327
They are thieves.

96
00:04:48,488 --> 00:04:49,476
They are thieves.

97
00:04:50,023 --> 00:04:51,639
They are not just here.
They live in my house!

98
00:04:51,725 --> 00:04:53,460
-They are in your house?
-Yes, they are.

99
00:04:53,873 --> 00:04:55,109
Come, let me show you.

100
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:58,164
This house was given to my grandmother

101
00:04:58,188 --> 00:05:01,077
because she was a refugee
from Haifa in 1948.

102
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:02,664
-This house.
-This one?

103
00:05:02,766 --> 00:05:04,754
It was built by my father in 2000

104
00:05:04,838 --> 00:05:08,003
because he got married and had children,
so he needed more space.

105
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:10,744
After my father finished building the house,
we were never allowed to live there.

106
00:05:10,893 --> 00:05:14,485
The judge came and sealed it permanently.

107
00:05:14,629 --> 00:05:18,637
He kept it sealed on the pretense
that it was built without a permit.

108
00:05:19,302 --> 00:05:22,896
-Who lives in it now?
-Settlers. Young men, not families.

109
00:05:22,923 --> 00:05:24,459
You live in that house?

110
00:05:24,540 --> 00:05:26,574
-They live here.
-And they live in this one?

111
00:05:26,665 --> 00:05:27,601
Exactly.

112
00:05:28,238 --> 00:05:31,645
Both my father and my mother
worked and saved to build this house.

113
00:05:31,729 --> 00:05:33,037
It was built with blood, sweat, and tears.

114
00:05:33,131 --> 00:05:35,540
And then the Israeli court

115
00:05:35,624 --> 00:05:39,181
issued a decree
allowing settlers to live in it.

116
00:05:39,301 --> 00:05:41,528
It's true that this house
was built without a permit

117
00:05:41,612 --> 00:05:43,014
and received two demolition orders.

118
00:05:43,359 --> 00:05:47,112
So, why would they allow
Israeli settlers to live in it

119
00:05:47,196 --> 00:05:49,262
and not me, the Palestinian?

120
00:05:49,316 --> 00:05:52,032
What sort of a democracy is this?

121
00:05:54,506 --> 00:05:55,574
How do you feel when you see him?

122
00:05:55,599 --> 00:05:56,369
Oppressed.

123
00:05:57,149 --> 00:05:58,187
Disturbed.

124
00:06:01,073 --> 00:06:02,638
It's annoying and exhausting.

125
00:06:07,119 --> 00:06:08,657
I don't cry because I'm weak.

126
00:06:08,943 --> 00:06:09,800
Never.

127
00:06:09,927 --> 00:06:10,983
Believe me.

128
00:06:11,405 --> 00:06:12,206
I swear.

129
00:06:12,590 --> 00:06:16,778
But I cry because we are not dealing
with a just state.

130
00:06:16,862 --> 00:06:18,043
This is an occupation.

131
00:06:19,166 --> 00:06:20,168
This is our land.

132
00:06:20,466 --> 00:06:23,182
I was born, raised, and have lived here.

133
00:06:23,483 --> 00:06:26,397
How can someone come and take it?
How does that make any sense?

134
00:06:26,665 --> 00:06:29,177
What's happening is a violation
of international law.

135
00:06:29,261 --> 00:06:31,184
This is a war crime.
Forced eviction is a war crime.

136
00:06:39,032 --> 00:06:39,843
Hello.

137
00:06:39,887 --> 00:06:41,514
-Hello. Hi.
-Hi, how are you?

138
00:06:42,027 --> 00:06:44,289
-Thank God. Still alive.
-Yeah.

139
00:06:44,638 --> 00:06:46,649
You're a difficult man to get hold of.

140
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,929
Yeah, I generally don't interview,

141
00:06:48,954 --> 00:06:52,287
but given the circumstances
and the bad press that's out there…

142
00:06:52,679 --> 00:06:55,746
decided that we need to
do some damage control.

143
00:06:55,888 --> 00:06:58,198
Jacob Fauci is an American Israeli.

144
00:06:58,282 --> 00:07:02,860
He became infamous after Muna
confronted him and the video went viral.

145
00:07:03,088 --> 00:07:05,412
Jacob, you know this is not your house!

146
00:07:05,496 --> 00:07:07,161
Yes, but if I go, you don't go back.

147
00:07:07,227 --> 00:07:08,816
So, what's the problem?
Why are you yelling at me?

148
00:07:08,862 --> 00:07:09,668
I didn't do this.

149
00:07:09,749 --> 00:07:12,261
You are stealing my house.

150
00:07:12,299 --> 00:07:14,134
And if I don't steal it,
someone else is going to steal it.

151
00:07:14,214 --> 00:07:18,822
No! No one--
No one is allowed to steal it, Jacob!

152
00:07:18,906 --> 00:07:22,687
He's been living in an additional
part of Muna's house for over ten years

153
00:07:22,776 --> 00:07:25,212
after being recruited
by a US-based company

154
00:07:25,251 --> 00:07:27,113
called Nahalat Shimon International

155
00:07:27,197 --> 00:07:29,768
which owns the property under Israeli law.

156
00:07:29,852 --> 00:07:31,394
How did you end up here?

157
00:07:31,418 --> 00:07:32,189
It's a long story.

158
00:07:32,213 --> 00:07:34,251
Basically, I needed to
move from where I was.

159
00:07:34,335 --> 00:07:37,601
And my friend was very very
active in this neighborhood.

160
00:07:37,691 --> 00:07:39,740
And he said you can stay
here for the time being.

161
00:07:39,765 --> 00:07:40,979
Do you pay rent?

162
00:07:41,183 --> 00:07:43,387
I have an arrangement
with the owners of the house.

163
00:07:43,427 --> 00:07:45,852
I don't wanna get into personal
arrangements and rents and things.

164
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:48,930
But yes, I'm a tenant here. I'm not--
I have no ownership over this property.

165
00:07:49,025 --> 00:07:50,790
-You're from Brooklyn?
-No, I'm from New York.

166
00:07:50,815 --> 00:07:52,081
-From Long Island.
-From New York.

167
00:07:52,165 --> 00:07:54,194
What right do you have to live here?

168
00:07:54,278 --> 00:07:57,640
The right I have is that the owner
of the house wants me to live here.

169
00:07:57,773 --> 00:08:00,211
And he wants there to be Jews
living in his house. And he wants--

170
00:08:00,295 --> 00:08:02,850
And I got chosen--
For whatever reason, it ended up being me.

171
00:08:03,057 --> 00:08:04,172
-We as a--
-So, why do you live here?

172
00:08:04,251 --> 00:08:05,622
Because I live here.
Because it's important.

173
00:08:05,647 --> 00:08:07,234
And because not too many
people want to live here.

174
00:08:07,284 --> 00:08:10,171
And it's important to strengthen
this neighborhood to make sure that

175
00:08:10,312 --> 00:08:13,263
this neighborhood is not
lost in any future peace deal.

176
00:08:14,239 --> 00:08:18,828
No, no to occupation.
Occupation will disappear!

177
00:08:18,912 --> 00:08:23,263
No, no to occupation.
Occupation will disappear!

178
00:08:23,354 --> 00:08:24,851
This is not their ancestral land.

179
00:08:24,935 --> 00:08:26,228
They've not been here for generations.

180
00:08:26,272 --> 00:08:28,416
They came here in 1956 because
they had nowhere else to be.

181
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:30,077
And somebody illegally put them here.

182
00:08:30,155 --> 00:08:32,631
Whatever they're accusing me of is…

183
00:08:32,794 --> 00:08:35,901
is no different from what they're doing
and what they did.

184
00:08:36,366 --> 00:08:39,926
So, your position here is a political
position to keep Palestinians out of it?

185
00:08:40,010 --> 00:08:41,973
Not to keep Palestinians out of it,
to keep Jews in it.

186
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:44,358
And therefore keep the
Palestinians who were here out of it.

187
00:08:44,434 --> 00:08:46,250
No-- That's not--
No.

188
00:08:46,260 --> 00:08:48,258
That's a--
That's a necessary evil.

189
00:08:49,242 --> 00:08:50,430
Whatever the situation is,

190
00:08:50,455 --> 00:08:52,696
and that's what I was trying
to explain in that viral video,

191
00:08:52,780 --> 00:08:54,013
they're not coming back here.

192
00:08:54,138 --> 00:08:55,969
This part of the house, for sure, is lost.

193
00:08:56,053 --> 00:08:58,320
The second part of the house,
unless there is some major miracle,

194
00:08:58,345 --> 00:08:59,479
is going to be lost.

195
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,234
And they're not coming back in here.

196
00:09:01,259 --> 00:09:03,083
So, whether I'm here,
whether I'm not here,

197
00:09:03,176 --> 00:09:04,391
whether it's me,
whether it's someone else,

198
00:09:04,415 --> 00:09:06,107
whether it's a monkey,
whether it's a giraffe,

199
00:09:06,191 --> 00:09:08,015
they're not coming
back into this house ever.

200
00:09:08,099 --> 00:09:10,861
I understand why they're angry at me.
I understand why they dislike me.

201
00:09:10,945 --> 00:09:12,962
But I did not do this to them.
I'm not doing this to them.

202
00:09:13,038 --> 00:09:16,051
And, as I said, if I leave,
I'll be replaced immediately.

203
00:09:16,089 --> 00:09:19,793
And I venture to think that whoever
comes here is not going to be as…

204
00:09:20,494 --> 00:09:21,962
easy-going as I am.

205
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:28,267
I've been instructed
to disperse the crowd.

206
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:32,795
Jacob's Nahalat Shimon International's
unyielding stance

207
00:09:32,872 --> 00:09:36,726
is being challenged both inside
the neighborhood and in court.

208
00:09:36,906 --> 00:09:39,259
Where lawyers representing
the families argue

209
00:09:39,343 --> 00:09:41,504
it's illegal under international law

210
00:09:41,588 --> 00:09:43,718
to displace anyone from occupied land.

211
00:09:44,570 --> 00:09:47,189
They're also arguing that
there's a double standard.

212
00:09:47,379 --> 00:09:50,219
Israel allows Jews
to return to their homeland,

213
00:09:50,303 --> 00:09:52,032
but not Palestinians.

214
00:09:52,194 --> 00:09:53,719
-Go over there!
-It's okay.

215
00:09:53,803 --> 00:09:55,494
-I don't want to cause a problem.
-You're in my way.

216
00:09:55,518 --> 00:09:56,771
-I just want to ask you, "Why?"
-Talk to me in Hebrew.

217
00:09:56,855 --> 00:09:57,964
-Over there. Go.
-I just--

218
00:09:57,988 --> 00:10:00,088
I wanna ask you why
you have taken the man.

219
