We found Abu Ayman Al Ghawi alone

223
00:10:18,496 --> 00:10:20,515
sitting outside his old house.

224
00:10:21,914 --> 00:10:24,554
So, you used to live in
this house across the road.

225
00:10:25,095 --> 00:10:26,110
What happened?

226
00:10:26,593 --> 00:10:30,697
They kicked us out
on the street in an hour.

227
00:10:31,153 --> 00:10:36,843
They destroyed the doors and beat us,
our children, and women.

228
00:10:38,572 --> 00:10:40,794
They forcefully threw us out.

229
00:10:41,630 --> 00:10:44,884
Were you given any help,
any money, a place to stay?

230
00:10:44,968 --> 00:10:46,761
What sort of support did you get?

231
00:10:47,092 --> 00:10:50,805
They didn't give us any assistance.
They didn't give us a flat or rent.

232
00:10:50,931 --> 00:10:53,578
Imagine, we have lived
here under this tree

233
00:10:53,691 --> 00:10:55,856
outside our flat for seven months.

234
00:10:55,936 --> 00:10:58,202
So, what happened to all your
belongings that were in the house?

235
00:10:58,369 --> 00:11:00,848
They took all the
furniture and dumped it.

236
00:11:00,894 --> 00:11:02,729
We don't know where
they took the furniture.

237
00:11:03,283 --> 00:11:07,302
We left with only the
clothes we were wearing.

238
00:11:07,948 --> 00:11:09,858
I was in my pajamas,

239
00:11:10,237 --> 00:11:13,445
and my wife left without slippers.

240
00:11:13,877 --> 00:11:16,224
How long exactly have
you lived in this house?

241
00:11:16,767 --> 00:11:19,495
I was born here in 1962.

242
00:11:19,585 --> 00:11:20,619
STOP OUR HOMES

243
00:11:20,644 --> 00:11:24,362
Jerusalem is our right,
not the settlers'.

244
00:11:24,981 --> 00:11:30,125
The settlers came from
America, Russia, and Germany.

245
00:11:30,196 --> 00:11:33,563
They don't have more of
a right to live here than me.

246
00:11:33,715 --> 00:11:37,824
I was born here, and my blood
and tears are in this house.

247
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:41,723
SHEIKH JARRAH

248
00:11:42,675 --> 00:11:44,355
Arieh King, a right-wing activist,

249
00:11:44,380 --> 00:11:47,689
who was appointed East Jerusalem's
Deputy Mayors last year,

250
00:11:47,908 --> 00:11:50,142
says the right belongs
to the Jewish people.

251
00:11:51,911 --> 00:11:53,562
When we are Jews

252
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:57,610
in the States, in Australia,
in England, in Jerusalem,

253
00:11:58,185 --> 00:11:59,645
we're facing towards one place.

254
00:12:01,688 --> 00:12:02,781
Haram al-Sharif.

255
00:12:02,839 --> 00:12:04,231
Mount-- Temple Mount.

256
00:12:04,256 --> 00:12:06,429
-I mean, that's religion.
-Of course.

257
00:12:06,590 --> 00:12:08,755
Talking about a religion

258
00:12:08,917 --> 00:12:12,089
when you're talking about people
and the land and where they live,

259
00:12:12,517 --> 00:12:13,565
is it relevant?

260
00:12:13,644 --> 00:12:14,554
Absolutely!

261
00:12:14,623 --> 00:12:18,237
So, you can't really justify ownership

262
00:12:18,544 --> 00:12:22,455
over religion when there are
so many different types of Arabs.

263
00:12:23,133 --> 00:12:26,568
Of course not.
But I'm just explaining what we are--

264
00:12:26,652 --> 00:12:29,259
The way that we see Jerusalem,

265
00:12:29,449 --> 00:12:32,071
it's a different way than any other…

266
00:12:32,586 --> 00:12:33,401
religion.

267
00:12:33,524 --> 00:12:35,004
As a Jew, you can live

268
00:12:35,373 --> 00:12:36,784
everywhere in the world,

269
00:12:37,123 --> 00:12:39,339
you can be the most orthodox Jew,

270
00:12:39,707 --> 00:12:42,043
if you don't live in Jerusalem,

271
00:12:42,501 --> 00:12:43,583
you cannot…

272
00:12:44,298 --> 00:12:47,905
keep the entire commitment of God.

273
00:12:50,739 --> 00:12:53,776
Do you want to see a Sheikh Jarrah…

274
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:55,408
that is…

275
00:12:56,864 --> 00:12:57,776
Jewish?

276
00:12:57,801 --> 00:12:58,681
Of course.

277
00:12:58,981 --> 00:13:00,403
Without Arabs?

278
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:02,722
I want to see Jews, yes.

279
00:13:09,689 --> 00:13:12,292
As the neighborhood
waits on the eviction appeal,

280
00:13:12,369 --> 00:13:13,897
support for the families is growing.

281
00:13:13,981 --> 00:13:15,383
This is our land!

282
00:13:15,491 --> 00:13:17,838
Police are getting more aggressive.

283
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:30,347
As it's getting closer, the smell
is getting really really strong.

284
00:13:36,115 --> 00:13:38,535
We can see everybody just ran inside.

285
00:13:38,885 --> 00:13:40,739
Because they don't want
to be sprayed with that.

286
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:41,874
It smells like sewage.

287
00:13:42,055 --> 00:13:43,653
Close it. Close it.

288
00:13:46,831 --> 00:13:49,868
One night, police even raided
a Palestinian resident's house…

289
00:13:50,257 --> 00:13:51,638
for playing loud music.

290
00:13:51,730 --> 00:13:55,978
Tell him to turn off the music!

291
00:13:56,062 --> 00:13:59,967
It's my house.

292
00:14:00,051 --> 00:14:02,638
-What are you doing?
-Come here. Come on!

293
00:14:02,722 --> 00:14:05,550
-Let me take him.
-Take him.

294
00:14:05,634 --> 00:14:09,761
Why? Tell him to turn the music off.

295
00:14:09,845 --> 00:14:13,422
-I want to go inside.
-Come on, move!

296
00:14:13,506 --> 00:14:14,749
Move away!

297
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:17,709
Close the door completely.

298
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:26,732
Don't open the door.

299
00:14:37,715 --> 00:14:39,314
Stay away from her!

300
00:14:46,801 --> 00:14:47,914
It's our house.

301
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:50,657
There is music here.

302
00:14:53,513 --> 00:14:55,160
Move!

303
00:14:58,799 --> 00:15:01,300
Move!

304
00:15:13,180 --> 00:15:15,429
Son of a bitch, go outside!

305
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:20,053
Get out!

306
00:15:22,014 --> 00:15:25,070
On another night,
police detained Muna's younger brother

307
00:15:25,158 --> 00:15:27,593
and held him for hours when
he was trying to go home.

308
00:15:27,771 --> 00:15:29,048
He lives here!

309
00:15:37,337 --> 00:15:38,718
Why are you pushing me?

310
00:15:38,778 --> 00:15:40,067
Calm down.

311
00:15:51,084 --> 00:15:52,632
Now do you know where he is?

312
00:15:52,986 --> 00:15:54,066
We don't know,

313
00:15:54,091 --> 00:15:57,131
but we're going to check
to see if he's at the police headquarters.

314
00:16:00,126 --> 00:16:01,617
You're the one who arrested my brother!

315
00:16:01,641 --> 00:16:04,407
May God not bless you! May God break
your arms, you animal! Son of a bitch!

316
00:16:15,475 --> 00:16:17,263
As Ramadan neared its end,

317
00:16:17,377 --> 00:16:19,754
Palestinians flocked to Al Aqsa Mosque.

318
00:16:19,916 --> 00:16:22,522
And the Israeli police
once again stormed in.

319
00:16:23,641 --> 00:16:27,099
ISRAEL POLICE VIA STORYFUL

320
00:16:31,769 --> 00:16:33,685
Hundreds of people were injured.

321
00:16:33,803 --> 00:16:35,911
But many medics were
prevented from entering.

322
00:16:36,002 --> 00:16:38,621
We've been outside for a while.
They wouldn't let us in.

323
00:16:38,665 --> 00:16:40,255
We've now made it into the grounds.

324
00:16:40,688 --> 00:16:45,150
There are the remnants of
stun grenades everywhere.

325
00:16:47,039 --> 00:16:48,617
East Jerusalem is at the heart

326
00:16:48,706 --> 00:16:50,982
of the Palestine-Israel conflict.

327
00:16:51,201 --> 00:16:52,367
And right now…

328
00:16:53,023 --> 00:16:54,378
it's exploded.

329
00:16:54,614 --> 00:16:55,981
Come inside! Come inside!

330
00:16:58,455 --> 00:17:02,128
The Palestinians are taking
refuge inside the Aqsa Mosque.

331
00:17:02,795 --> 00:17:05,165
God is great!

332
00:17:12,376 --> 00:17:15,057
While Palestinians barricaded
themselves in the mosque,

333
00:17:15,301 --> 00:17:18,465
close by, right-wing Israelis,
including Arieh King,

334
00:17:19,173 --> 00:17:22,875
celebrated the date Israel
captured Jerusalem in 1967.

335
00:17:26,372 --> 00:17:27,960
A lot is happening right now.

336
00:17:27,981 --> 00:17:32,125
Al Aqsa, what you call Jerusalem Day,
Sheikh Jarrah.

337
00:17:32,307 --> 00:17:34,805
Do you think that
this is a very delicate moment?

338
00:17:34,889 --> 00:17:37,691
It's a delicate moment like many
other moments that we have here.

339
00:17:38,325 --> 00:17:40,474
And we've passed many moments like that…

340
00:17:40,805 --> 00:17:42,563
and we'll pass this also.

341
00:17:42,945 --> 00:17:44,781
What do you want to see in the end?

342
00:17:45,090 --> 00:17:46,547
What would make you happy?

343
00:17:47,222 --> 00:17:48,793
To see the temple built…

344
00:17:49,801 --> 00:17:53,573
at the temple mark where
there is the Dome of the Rock.

345
00:17:53,728 --> 00:17:55,235
In the holy of holiness…

346
00:17:55,943 --> 00:17:56,958
we believe,

347
00:17:57,123 --> 00:17:58,545
and we trust God,

348
00:17:58,796 --> 00:17:59,915
and we believe God,

349
00:17:59,939 --> 00:18:01,836
So, we trust that it will happen.

350
00:18:01,979 --> 00:18:05,272
And we need to do everything
to ensure it happens in our days.

351
00:18:11,057 --> 00:18:12,192
2021-05-13
THURSDAY 14:27:16

352
00:18:12,224 --> 00:18:15,128
In retaliation, for the
storming of the Al Aqsa,

353
00:18:15,223 --> 00:18:18,138
Hamas, the Palestinian
militant group that governs Gaza,

354
00:18:18,237 --> 00:18:19,610
fired on Israel.

355
00:18:19,997 --> 00:18:23,717
At least 13 civilians had been killed,
including two children.

356
00:18:23,791 --> 00:18:24,862
GAZA CITY

357
00:18:24,887 --> 00:18:28,373
Israel responded with a
disproportionate show of force

358
00:18:28,476 --> 00:18:30,385
leveling apartment
buildings and newsrooms.

359
00:18:30,410 --> 00:18:33,401
In one of the most densely
populated places on earth,

360
00:18:33,519 --> 00:18:35,406
to escape is impossible.

361
00:18:35,490 --> 00:18:38,727
Israel has closed off the
crossing into the blockaded strip.

362
00:18:41,446 --> 00:18:46,917
So far, over 200 Palestinians have
been killed, including 61 children.

363
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:51,172
When the bombing stops

364
00:18:51,446 --> 00:18:54,325
and the international
community is no longer watching,

365
00:18:54,350 --> 00:18:56,436
Muna will still be fighting,

366
00:18:56,503 --> 00:18:59,179
including Israel's Supreme Court.

367
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:03,182
The residents of Sheikh Jarrah say

368
00:19:03,264 --> 00:19:05,909
court cases like this
happen on a monthly basis.

369
00:19:05,993 --> 00:19:08,375
But they still say despite the
amount of times they've been here,

370
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,726
they have no faith in the justice system.

371
00:19:18,360 --> 00:19:20,085
They say it's their land,

372
00:19:20,710 --> 00:19:22,777
and we say that it's not their land.

373
00:19:23,562 --> 00:19:24,826
In the coming weeks,

374
00:19:25,088 --> 00:19:29,168
the courts will make a decision on the
cases of 28 families appealing eviction.

375
00:19:29,631 --> 00:19:32,271
If they lose, they'll be left homeless.

376
00:19:32,573 --> 00:19:36,530
When you sat inside there,
as a Palestinian in an Israeli court,

377
00:19:36,613 --> 00:19:38,059
do you feel the same as them?

378
00:19:38,115 --> 00:19:39,337
Do you feel equal to them?

379
00:19:39,345 --> 00:19:43,304
I feel that even my most basic right,

380
00:19:43,382 --> 00:19:45,835
having an Arabic translator,
was not given to me.

381
00:19:45,986 --> 00:19:49,302
In the end, we're dealing with
a system of settlers.

382
00:19:49,489 --> 00:19:54,567
They don't want us
Palestinians to stay in our land.

383
00:19:54,651 --> 00:19:56,485
They want to make Jerusalem
the unified capital of Israel

384
00:19:56,762 --> 00:20:02,418
and they want to do an ethnic cleansing
of all the Palestinians in Jerusalem.

385
00:20:03,184 --> 00:20:06,503
We will not give our homes to them.

386
00:20:06,571 --> 00:20:07,586
No way!

387
00:20:07,830 --> 00:20:11,643
I always say that I would
chain myself to the house.

388
00:20:11,712 --> 00:20:13,528
I won't leave.
They'd better come and drag me out of it.

